author: pburba
msg: Port of svn command line via svn:// for OS/400.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_svn/client.c
(make_connection): Pass ebcdic hostname to apr_sockaddr_info_get.
(ra_svn_open): Pass ebcdic url to apr_uri_parse and convert string members of
returned uri to utf-8.

author: pburba
msg: Port prompt functionality to OS/400 qsh environment.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/prompt.c
Include svn_ebcdic.h and svn_utf.h.
(USERNAME_STR): New utf-8 hex escaped symbolic constant.
(prompt): Replace svn_cmdline_fputs with SVN_CMDLINE_FPRINTF2 making utf-8
encoded prompt_msg to go to stderr as ebcdic.  Also strip any LF appended to
strbuf->data by qsh (or IBM's implementation of apr_password_get?).
(maybe_print_realm): Replace svn_cmdline_fprintf with SVN_CMDLINE_FPRINTF2
allowing utf-8 var args to go the stderr as ebcdic.
(svn_cl__auth_simple_prompt): USe SVN_UTF8_* symbolic constants and new
symbol place of string literal.  Replace apr_psprintf with APR_PSPRINTF2
allowing utf-8 var args.
(svn_cl__auth_username_prompt): Use SVN_UTF8_* symbolic constants and new
symbol.

author: pburba
msg: Port of svn cleaunup for OS/400.
Disable the --diff3-cmd option as we have no plans to support that in the port.
* subversion/clients/cmdline/main.c
(svn_cl__cmd_table): Disable --diff3-cmd for svn switch.
